# SecureNotesApp

This application is intended for encrypted notes using AES. In the login window password should be provided as battery
percentage. The encrypted notes are locally saved on device (using shared preferences).


 
# Description:

When openning the application, a login window appears. The password is the battery precentage in device. 
After logging in, the notes were already saved before, will be decrypted and shown in the notes list screen.

Each existing note in the list is now can be read or edited. 
At the bottom of the notes list screen there is an '+' button to create a new note.

Clicking on existing note/new note will lead to the note screen. 
After creating/editing note's content the whole data will be re-encrypted and updated to both notes list screen and device memory.

Re-encrypting the data after every change will provide strong detection.







